TEN people were injured on the M13 in Durban Bound Fields Hill in Pinetown after a head on collision in the early hours of Monday morning. Rescue Care Paramedics spokesperson, Garrith Jamieson said when they arrived on the scene they found the badly damaged vehicles on the road. Jamieson said there were multiple causalities lying in the middle of the road. “Immediately more ambulances as well as Advanced Life Support Paramedics were dispatched to assist with the scene. A total of ten people had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious and once all were stabilised on the scene they were transported to various Durban Hospitals for the further care that they required,” Jamieson said. At this stage the events leading up to the crash are unknown. Jamieson the South African Police Services (SAPS) were on the scene and are investigating further.  